  - q: "Can I train while wearing the aligners?"
    a: "Yes. Aligners stay in during training. Many runners report better nasal breathing and less jaw tension under effort."
  - q: "What about a marathon or multi-day race?"
    a: "We hand you the next sets ahead of time with a change calendar. You travel without breaking your treatment. A rugged travel case is part of the kit."
  - q: "Do I need to pause for race week?"
    a: "No. We schedule refinements and aligner deliveries around your race calendar. You keep training, we adapt."
  - q: "How does nasal breathing improve?"
    a: "A balanced bite and arch usually improve lip sealing and nasal breathing. If you mouth-breathe under effort, we may also flag a myofunctional/speech evaluation."
